The paper discusses the application of machine learning in wildfire science and management, which falls under the domain of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of various ML algorithms such as random forests, decision trees, and support vector machines, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of ML in mapping and detection, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of ML in predicting fire behavior, which requires computational modeling (cs.CE) and the use of high-performance computing (cs.DC). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.AI, cs.CE, cs.LG, cs.DC, and cs.CV, in that order.
